{
  "id": "asm-in-memory-db",
  "kind": "problem",
  "title": "Progressive In-Memory Database",
  "difficulty": "medium",
  "concepts": [
    "simulation",
    "stateful design",
    "hash map",
    "snapshot"
  ],
  "prompt": "Implement an in-memory store driven by an operation list. `solution(queries)` receives a list of queries; each query is a list of strings `[OP, timestamp, ...args]`. Every query has a non-negative integer `timestamp` (string-encoded), even when this level doesn't use it. Return a list with one string result per query, in order.\n\nThe store is keyed two levels deep: `store[key][field] = value`. Keys and fields are case-sensitive strings.\n\n**Level 1 operations**\n\n- `[\"SET\", timestamp, key, field, value]` — set `store[key][field] = value`, creating `store[key]` if needed. Always return `\"true\"`.\n- `[\"GET\", timestamp, key, field]` — return the value if `key` and `field` both exist, else return `\"\"`.\n- `[\"DELETE\", timestamp, key, field]` — if both exist, remove the field (and the key itself if no fields remain) and return `\"true\"`. Otherwise return `\"false\"`.\n\nLater levels add filtering, TTL, and time-aware snapshots to this same function. Structure it as a clean per-op dispatcher so those extensions can slot in.",
  "signature": {
    "name": "solution",
    "inputs": [
      {
        "name": "queries",
        "type": {
          "type": "array",
          "items": {
            "type": "array",
            "items": {
              "type": "string"
            }
          }
        }
      }
    ],
    "output": {
      "type": "array",
      "items": {
        "type": "string"
      }
    }
  },
  "tests": [
    {
      "name": "l1-empty",
      "args": [
        []
      ],
      "expected": [],
      "visibility": "visible"
    },
    {
      "name": "l1-set-then-get",
